This paper deals with the problem of detecting a parameter vector in a linear model, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the success probability of two different detectors, which involves probability theory and statistical analysis, making it relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY).
